    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-25T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-25T01:00:00-05:00" n="341"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">886A.2553/4–2554: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 341<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Saudi Arabia (<persName corresp="#p_WG1"
                            type="from">Wadsworth</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d341fn1">Repeated to Dhahran.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-25T09:00:00+03:00"
                            >April 25, 1954—9 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>442. 1. Following is text Royal Decree No. 6/6/3/5737 of April 9 (as carried in
                        <hi rend="italic">Al Bilad Al Saudiyah</hi> April 23) ratifying agreement
                    negotiated between Minister Finance and A. S. Onassis for formation Saudi
                    Arabian Maritime Company and Transport Saudi Oil (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 439, April 20 and previous):<note n="2" xml:id="d341fn2">Not
                        printed. (886A.2553/4–2054)</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“We Saud Ibn Abdul Aziz Ibn Abdul Rahman Al Faisal Al Saud King of Saudi
                            Arabian Kingdom relying on God and being acquainted with agreement
                            consisting of sixteen clauses and two exchange letters enclosed with
                            agreement which had been signed by our order in Jidda on date 15/5/1373
                            corresponding to January 20, 1954 between our Finance Minister and A. S.
                            Onassis on behalf himself (Onassis) and companies which he represents
                            have ordered following: <list>
                                <item>First article: We confirm above said agreement which is
                                    enclosed with this decree and we order it be put into effect on
                                    date of our decree.</item>
                                <item>Second article: Deputy President of Council of Ministers will
                                    execute this decree.</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                        <p>Issued from our Palace in Riyadh on sixth Shaban 1373 corresponding to
                            April 9, 1954”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>2. <gloss target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> Vice President <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJT1">Duce</persName> with whom I discussed decree today has
                    telegraphed following comment to Board Chairman <persName corresp="#p_DFA1"
                        >Davies</persName> Dhahran: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In my view this matter is of critical importance not only to us but to
                            whole industry.</p>
                        <p>I presume we shall shortly receive from <gloss target="#t_SAG1"
                                >SAG</gloss> due notice regarding enforcement this decree and that
                            full text Onassis contract will be made available.</p>
                        <p>I believe that if contract says what we have reason to believe it says we
                            should consider notifying <gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> we may be
                            forced to cut <pb facs="0853" n="813" xml:id="pg_813"/> back production
                            to amount which can be lifted by parent company tankers.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>3. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 303 April 23<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d341fn3">Not printed, but see <ref target="#d340fn3">footnote 3, <hi
                                rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>. Telegram 445 from Jidda, Apr. 26, informed the Department of State
                        the Ambassador had called at the Saudi Arabian Foreign Office on that day to
                        request official copies of the Onassis agreement and express his misgivings
                        about it. (886A.2553/4–2654)</note> was received after foregoing drafted.
                    Will consult further with <persName corresp="#p_DJT1">Duce</persName> before
                    replying.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
